==Production==

===Filming===
[[Principal photography]] on ''Bala Bala Sese'' began late 2012 and wrapped 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://matookerepublic.com/2015/04/23/a-pass-wuuyo-video-is-snippet-of-upcoming-bala-bala-sese-movie/|title=A Pass’ Wuuyo video is snippet of upcoming Bala Bala Sese movie|first=Matooke|last=Republic|date=23 April 2015|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> The movie was filmed on the [[Ssese Islands]] in [[Uganda]], from which it takes its name.<ref name="auto"/>

==Release==
The film was released on 3 July 2015 at theatre Labonita.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observer.ug/lifestyle/42-entertainment/38552-natasha-michael-set-to-relive-romance-on-screen|title=Natasha, Michael set to relive romance on screen|first=Andrew|last=Kaggwa|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chano8.com/glitz-and-glamour-at-the-premiere-of-bala-bala-sese-movie/|title=Glitz and Glamour At The Premiere Of Bala Bala Sese Movie|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> Bala Bala Sese is rather the very first Ugandan project to receive a professional marketing approach and one of the top local productions of that year and the following year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news24africa.com/ugandan-cinema-slowly-getting-deserved-attention/|title=Ugandan cinema slowly getting deserved attention|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/artsculture/Entertainment/Bala-Bala-Ssese-movie-premieres/-/812796/2776022/-/144lm1p/-/index.html/|title=Bala Bala Ssese movie premieres|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> It was nominated in the [[12th Africa Movie Academy Awards]] for [[Africa Movie Academy Award for Best Film in an African Language|Best Film in an African Language]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmcontact.com/news/nigeria/africa-movie-academy-announces-full-list-2016-nominations|title=Africa Movie Academy announces full list of 2016 Nominations|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> It held its African premiere at the Luxor African Film Festival in Cairo, Egypt and competed in the long Narrative category among 13 other African films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theinsider.ug/ugandan-films-vie-for-4000-prize-at-luxor-festival/|title=Ugandan films vie for $4,000 prize at Luxor festival – theinsider.ug|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.luxorafricanfilmfestival.com/en/Festival/Film/Long%20Narrative/Bala%20Bala%20Sese/|title=LAFF - Long Narrative|website=www.luxorafricanfilmfestival.com|language=en|access-date=2018-09-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observer.ug/lifestyle/42-entertainment/42547-ugandan-films-for-international-festivals|title=Ugandan films for international festivals|first=Andrew|last=Kaggwa|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> It was the opening film at the 10 [[Amakula International Film Festival]] and automatically qualified for the Golden Impala Award in the best African film which was won by ''De Noir''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://amakula.org/film/bala-bala-sese-uganda/|title=Bala Bala Sese - Uganda - Amakula|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://proggie.ug/amakula-international-film-festival-returns/#.VtWM5qbARMg.facebook/|title=AMAKULA International Film Festival Returns - Proggie - Events in and around Kampala!|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref>

===Music and soundtrack===
The soundtrack album for Bala Bala Sese was composed by Nessim with the official theme song [[Wuuyo]] recorded by [[A Pass]] and Nessim again of Badi Musik. The song became the singer's most successful single todate. The official video of the song premiered on 20 March 2015 at Club Guvnor and features clips from the movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chano8.com/a-pass-wuuyo-soundtrack-for-the-bala-bala-sese-movie/|title=A pass' Wuuyo Soundtrack For The Bala Bala Sese Movie - Chano8|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bigeye.ug/a-pass-wuyo-to-be-used-as-soundtrack-in-a-local-movie/|title=A-Pass’ Wuyo to be used as soundtrack in a local movie.|date=26 March 2015|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.celebcartel.com/a-pass-wuyo-to-be-used-as-soundtrack-in-a-local-movie/|title=celebcartel.com|publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref>

==Awards==

===Nominated===
* 2016: Long Narrative, Luxor African Film Festival
* 2016: Golden Impala Award, [[Amakula International Film Festival]]
* 2016: [[Africa Movie Academy Award for Best Film in an African Language|Best Film in an African Language]], [[12th Africa Movie Academy Awards]]
* 2016: Helsinki African Film Festival Jury Award for Human Rights and Social Commentary.<ref>haff.fi/2016/en/haff-2016-jury-awards/</ref>
* 2016: Best Feature Film, [[Africa International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://afriff.com/2016-home/afriff-2016-final-selection/|title=Final Selection|work=AFRIFF|access-date=2018-09-12|language=en-US}}</ref>

The motion picture has also been named as one of the best films of 2015 and 2016 by various ongoing critics.

* 4th&nbsp;– Anicee Gohar, ''Scoop Empire''
* 4th&nbsp;– Elizabeth Mcsheffrey, ''British Airways, Highlife''
* 1st&nbsp;– Douglas Sebamala, ''Monitor Uganda''

